## Example 5: People, Technology — Finding the Right Balance in AI-Driven Incident Management
**URL**: https://cutover.com/blog/people-technology-finding-right-balance-ai-driven-incident-management
**Topic**: The human-AI balance in incident management — when to automate, when to keep humans in the loop
**Audience**: Major Incident Managers, CIO, Head of Ops

### What to replicate
- Acknowledge the tension openly: AI is powerful, but full autonomy in a live outage is dangerous
- Use the "Assistive Mode → Supervised Autonomy → Full Autonomy" progression as a structure
- Validate the reader's concern (loss of control, black-box decisions) before offering the answer
- The resolution: **humans stay in the loop**, AI earns trust incrementally
- Close with an empowering message: this isn't about replacing your team, it's about making them better

